In an effort to minimize the differnce, I created a plot of the difference
 between the measures as a function of the measured magnitude, for option
 2 (see figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:The-diffrence-as"

\end_inset

, blue).
 We noticed the the difference grows significantly when the measured magnitude
 exceeds 20-21 Mag.
 To minimize this effect, I clipped all the measurments in each band that
 have a value higher than 20.5 Mag (see figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:The-diffrence-as"

\end_inset

, red).
 We can notice that after the clipping, the plots show an approximately
 straight line with the constant value of 0 (in some bands exists a small
 shift above 0, e.g.
 band r), so the differences are small enough.
 After clipping, I added to the median and std table the values after clipping
 (Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:The-medians-and"

\end_inset

, 2 rightest columns).
 We can notice that for option option 1 the values barely change, whereas
 for option 2 there is a significant change (between 2.5%-12%).
 
\end_layout

